cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of data race prediction in software programs, which is a common concern in programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents algorithms for identifying data race pairs, which involves logical reasoning and scheduling (cs.LO) as well as computational complexity (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
